description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The East Suffolk and North Essex NHS Foundation Trust has an exciting and challenging opportunity for an experienced equality, diversity and inclusion (ED&amp;I) lead to define and drive our ED&amp;I strategy with the full support of our senior leadership teams and key stakeholders. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As a successful ED&amp;I leader, you will be at the forefront of driving real change throughout the organisation to support the creation of a positive culture where all our patients will experience outstanding care which meets their specific needs, with a workforce where no-one will feel compelled to conceal their identity for fear of stigma and where people can be authentic and feel valued.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal discussion please contact the Recruitment Team on 01206 745280 or email Kelly.Turner3@esneft.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
